Relevance: movement-verified dismissal (step/walk requirement) for users who snooze in-bed.\n- Sleep Cycle — https://apps.apple.com/us/app/sleep-cycle-sleep-tracker/id320606217?xs=1\n  - Relevance: large incumbent wake-up/sleep utility; useful baseline for “big but lower-friction” comparison.\n\n## Recent review themes and user signals (bounded to available evidence)\n- Common complaints\n  - Paywall/subscription fatigue appears repeatedly in high-friction alarm category listings.\n  - Reliability anxiety remains a core user fear: “alarm won’t fire loudly/consistently” concern drives churn risk.\n  - Ad intrusiveness is a pain point in free variants (especially during alarm flows).\n  - Anti-cheat gaps: users find ways to bypass tasks if challenge design is too predictable.\n- Frequent feature requests\n  - Better challenge variety without cognitive overload right after wake-up.\n  - Smarter progressive friction (easy on low-risk days, strict on critical mornings).\n  - Better wearable/support integrations and fallback alarms.\n  - Family/accountability sharing (partner/friend confirmation, missed-alarm escalation).\n- Delight moments\n  - Users praise alarms that force physical context-switch (scan in bathroom/kitchen, walk steps).\n  - “Cannot accidentally dismiss” experiences are consistently valued by chronic snoozers.\n  - Simple setup + strong default missions appears to improve first-week retention.\n\n## Fast-growing vs merely large\n- Appears merely large/incumbent\n  - Sleep Cycle: broad sleep utility and strong brand footprint; not narrowly optimized for punitive anti-snooze behavior.\n- Appears fast-growing/emergent in adjacent anti-habit enforcement\n  - one sec, ScreenZen, Opal (from local Consumer Radar fixtures) show acceleration patterns around behavioral friction loops.\n  - Why it matters: these apps suggest users reward “interrupt autopilot” mechanics, which transfers to wake-up accountability design.\n- Alarm niche implication\n  - Differentiation opportunity is not “another alarm list UI,” but trustable high-friction outcomes with visible proof and escalation.\n\n## Concrete product opportunities for WakeTask\n- Adaptive Friction Ladder\n  - Start with low-cognitive wake checks, escalate to movement + scan + timed micro-task if snooze repeats.\n- Reliability-First Alarm Engine UX\n  - Pre-flight check before bedtime (volume route, focus state, permissions, backup trigger readiness) with plain-language pass/fail.\n- Accountability Escalation Graph\n  - If user misses threshold, trigger staged accountability: self-commitment proof -> buddy nudge -> stake event.\n- “No-cheat by design” Missions\n  - Rotation pool with anti-repetition controls, randomization windows, and post-dismiss verification.\n- Critical-Morning Mode\n  - Per-alarm strictness profiles (exam/workflight/day) with harsher dismissal requirements only when needed.\n- Post-wake Outcome Loop\n  - Capture “awake proof” + 3-minute intent task (first action) to convert alarm success into day-start consistency.\n\n## Sources used\n- https://apps.apple.com/us/app/alarmy-alarm-clock-sleep/id1163786766?platform=iphone\n- https://apps.apple.com/us/app/challenges-alarm-clock/id1247289889\n- https://apps.apple.com/us/app/barcode-alarm-clock/id699437630\n- https://apps.apple.com/us/app/barcode-alarm-clock-pro/id731358084\n- https://apps.apple.com/gb/app/nuj-alarm-clock/id1557053396\n- https://apps.apple.com/us/app/walk-me-up-alarm-clock-free/id1022744160\n- https://apps.apple.com/us/app/sleep-cycle-sleep-tracker/id320606217?xs=1\n- local artifact: `.workflow/consumer-radar/data-source-smoke.json`\n- local artifact: `apps/generated-consumer-app-radar/.data/apps.json`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
